<docs>
	<doc for="CompilerGlobalScopeAttribute.CompilerGlobalScopeAttribute">
		<summary>
			<para>Initializes a new instance of the
 <see langword="CompilerGlobalScopeAttribute"/> class.</para>
		</summary>
	</doc><doc for="CompilerGlobalScopeAttribute">
		<summary>
			<para> Indicates that a class should be treated as if it has
      global scope.</para>
		</summary>
		<remarks>
			<para> You can apply this attribute to classes.</para>
			<para> This class is used only for communication with debugger tools.</para>
			<para>The classes in System.Runtime.CompilerServices are for
   compiler writers use only.</para>
		</remarks>
	</doc></docs>
